summary: T-NER is an open-source Python library for Transformer-based Named Entity Recognition (NER) that enables fine-tuning language models and facilitates cross-domain and cross-lingual analysis. It features easy-to-use tools for model training, evaluation, and interactive predictions, while also providing insights into domain-specific learning and releasing pretrained checkpoints for future research.
